# 1. Have you ever been part of a sports team?

Yes, I have. When I was in high school, I was actually a member of the basketball team for about two years. Although I wasn’t the best player, I really enjoyed the experience because it taught me a lot about teamwork and discipline. We used to train after class almost every day, and sometimes we took part in local competitions. Looking back, I think being on a team helped me become more confident and better at communicating with other people.

### 中文翻译：

有的。我高中时曾经加入过学校篮球队，大概待了两年。虽然我不是队里最厉害的球员，但我真的很享受那段经历，因为它让我学会了团队合作和纪律性。我们以前几乎每天放学后都会训练，有时候还会参加一些校际比赛。现在回想起来，我觉得加入球队让我变得更自信，也更擅长与别人沟通。

---

# 2. Is team sports popular in your culture?

Yes, definitely. Team sports are very popular in China, especially among students and young people. For example, basketball and football are probably the most common sports played on school campuses. I think one reason is that team sports are not only entertaining, but they also help people build friendships and reduce stress from study or work. In recent years, with the influence of professional leagues and social media, more and more people have started following team sports regularly.

### 中文翻译：

是的，绝对很受欢迎。团队运动在中国非常流行，尤其是在学生和年轻人之间。比如篮球和足球可能是校园里最常见的运动。我觉得其中一个原因是团队运动不仅有趣，而且还能帮助人们建立友谊、缓解学习和工作的压力。近几年随着职业联赛和社交媒体的发展，越来越多的人开始持续关注团队运动。

---

# 3. Do you like watching team games? Why?

Yes, I do, especially basketball matches. I enjoy watching team games because they’re usually exciting and unpredictable. Unlike some individual sports, team games involve cooperation, tactics, and quick decision-making, which makes them more intense to watch. As someone who is interested in competition and strategy, I find it fascinating to see how players work together under pressure. Besides that, watching games with friends creates a really energetic atmosphere, so it’s also a social activity for me.

### 中文翻译：

喜欢，尤其是篮球比赛。我喜欢看团队比赛，因为它们通常很刺激，而且结果往往难以预测。和一些个人项目相比，团队比赛涉及配合、战术以及快速决策，所以观赏性更强。作为一个对竞争和策略比较感兴趣的人，我觉得观察球员如何在压力下协作非常有意思。而且和朋友一起看比赛氛围也特别热闹，所以它对我来说也是一种社交活动。

---

# 4. What are the differences between team sports and individual sports?

I think the biggest difference is responsibility. In team sports, success depends on cooperation among all the players, so communication and teamwork are extremely important. However, in individual sports, athletes rely more on their own ability and mental strength. Another difference is the pressure people experience. In individual sports, if you fail, you can’t really blame anyone else, while in team sports the responsibility is shared. Personally, I think both types of sports are valuable because they develop different skills and personalities.

### 中文翻译：

我觉得最大的区别在于“责任感”。在团队运动中，成功依赖于所有队员之间的配合，所以沟通和团队协作特别重要。而在个人运动中，运动员更多依靠自己的能力和心理素质。另一个区别是人们承受的压力不同。在个人项目里，如果失败了，基本没办法怪别人；但在团队项目中，责任是大家共同承担的。就我个人而言，我觉得这两类运动都很有价值，因为它们培养的是不同的能力和性格。
